project-localized-name-pnbwiki: This is the localized project name for [https://pnb.wikipedia.org Shahmukhi Punjabi Wikipedia]. These names are not embedded in a sentence. For example, they can be used as a standalone heading. Translate all parts, including proper names (e.g. country names). The translated language name from CLDR is "Western Punjabi," however this term is incorrect and is not used outside of English. On the Wikipedia itself, the project is simply described as Punjabi Wikipedia, and as Shahmukhi Wikipedia to distinguish it from Gurmukhi Punjabi Wikipedia, the site for the other widely used script of the language. This message may not contain any wikitext markup nor HTML.
